1
00:00:48,220 --> 00:00:52,960
[The Ferry Man: 10th Anniversary]

2
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:56,060
[Episode 6]

3
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:58,070
Let me see.

4
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,130
We really can't complete the task.

5
00:01:09,590 --> 00:01:10,320
This town...

6
00:01:10,510 --> 00:01:11,350
is haunted.

7
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,760
I strongly advise you

8
00:01:13,950 --> 00:01:15,150
to steer away from it.

9
00:01:15,150 --> 00:01:16,640
Even if you can build villas there,

10
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:18,300
you won't be able to sell them.

11
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:19,820
I'll pay you in full

12
00:01:19,950 --> 00:01:21,210
and waive the penalty,

13
00:01:21,310 --> 00:01:23,310
since you didn't deliberately
breach the contract.

14
00:01:23,310 --> 00:01:23,710
Great.

15
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:25,560
-Thank you, Ms. Huang.
-Thanks, Ms. Huang.

16
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:26,200
Remember

17
00:01:26,950 --> 00:01:28,350
to keep your mouths shut.

18
00:01:32,310 --> 00:01:32,950
Let's go.

19
00:01:43,789 --> 00:01:44,200
Hello.

20
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,130
Is it Xia Dongqing?

21
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,400
Fancy making some money?

22
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:58,729
You're looking to develop a town,

23
00:01:58,759 --> 00:02:00,350
but there exist some dirty things

24
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:01,880
that need to be cleared out.

25
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:05,250
You believe in
all that supernatural stuff?

26
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:08,470
Many people can't see those beings,

27
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:09,080
but that

28
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:11,080
doesn't mean they don't exist.

29
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,010
Can you see them?

30
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:12,900
No, I can't.

31
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,920
You go beyond merely believing they exist.

32
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,120
Last time, when your mother's soul

33
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,050
appeared there,

34
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,510
you seemed to have...

35
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,190
Grown accustomed to it.

36
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:21,590
Right, accustomed to it.

37
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,870
"I command the green demon of pestilence
from the east—

38
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:25,870
the spirit of rotten wood;

39
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,310
the red demon of pestilence
from the south—

40
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:28,310
the spirit of flame;

41
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,590
the blood demon of pestilence—

42
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,750
the spirit of vile gold;

43
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:33,550
and the black demon of pestilence
from the north."

44
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,240
One of my family legacies is a book.

45
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,520
I read it when I was little.

46
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,430
There are all sorts of spells in it.

47
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:41,630
What is your mother's surname?

48
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:42,190
Huang.

49
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,560
So you took your mother's surname?

50
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:45,590
I see.

51
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,090
You are a witch then.

52
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,800
The role of a witch is passed down
through the female line.

53
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,600
You carry your mother's surname.

54
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,000
In each generation of your family,

55
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,829
a girl would be born

56
00:02:53,829 --> 00:02:55,150
with special powers.

57
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,079
I have no special powers.

58
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,780
Now, back to the topic.

59
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:02,360
My family's ancestral home
is in that town.

60
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:02,960
However,

61
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,960
no one has ever gone back there
since my great-grandmother's

62
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,560
generation left that place.

63
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,280
If your ancestral home is demolished,

64
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,540
won't it be a huge pity?

65
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,410
Her mother has asked her

66
00:03:11,590 --> 00:03:13,320
for a word about another issue.

67
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:16,030
By that, she means to stop me
from developing the town.

68
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,310
You won't listen to her anyway.

69
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:18,280
Right, I won't.

70
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:21,150
Starting from
my great-grandmother's generation,

71
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:22,840
my entire family has been living
in Nanyang.

72
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,630
My mother didn't

73
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:25,560
return here until several years ago.

74
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,710
She only visits that place occasionally
to reminisce.

75
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:29,970
Jiangnan towns like it are a dime a dozen.

76
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:30,960
That place isn't worth

77
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,560
developing for tourism at all.

78
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,360
Nonetheless,

79
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:35,960
all will be different
when villas are built.

80
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,190
They'll be surrounded by hills and rivers
that provide perfect scenery.

81
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:39,920
Immense value will be created.

82
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,660
It'll be much better this way
than lying wasted.

83
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:43,840
You are a witch.

84
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,400
That place doesn't scare you.

85
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,910
Why not check out the town on your own?

86
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:47,630
Come on,

87
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,370
my time is rather precious.

88
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,360
So much money?

89
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,110
It's for you two to split.

90
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,410
Let me make it clear.

91
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,080
Evil spirits are causing

92
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,480
trouble in that town.

93
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,940
When I was a child, I vaguely heard

94
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:10,000
that a powerful demon

95
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,190
was sealed there.

96
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,630
A powerful demon?

97
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:17,390
The world

98
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:20,510
is full of strange things.

99
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:08,800
Dongqing.

100
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:11,070
What took you so long?

101
00:05:11,070 --> 00:05:11,930
Open the trunk.

102
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,270
What's in it?

103
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,040
Tools.

104
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:28,940
Get in the car.

105
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:35,800
How amazing.

106
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,070
My followers

107
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,630
now amount to nine million.

108
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,180
Congratulations.

109
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,790
Now, ninety-eight percent

110
00:05:41,790 --> 00:05:42,750
of your followers

111
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,630
are female.

112
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,240
Thank you so much, Ya.

113
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,120
I can feel energy

114
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:49,790
surging through my body now.

115
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,310
I am getting closer and closer

116
00:05:51,310 --> 00:05:52,430
to reaching my goal.

117
00:05:52,430 --> 00:05:53,760
I'm truly happy for you.

118
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:10,630
Why are you being such a good boy?

119
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,720
Because

120
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,290
I want to please you.

121
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:15,420
Because I love you.

122
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,410
Love me for what?

123
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:21,200
For your beauty.

124
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:39,810
Your demon core...

125
00:07:40,990 --> 00:07:42,590
It was made with a human life.

126
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:44,010
Quite formidable.

127
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,320
That woman doesn't trust me.

128
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:49,680
So what?

129
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,250
Will she ever resist your temptation?

130
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:55,400
She will obey my every word.

131
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,240
Let's go.

132
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,730
Why are you looking at me like that?

133
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,550
You seem completely different.

134
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,510
Different how?

135
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,210
I'm not like a nerd anymore?

136
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,679
You resemble Zhao Li even more now.

137
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:38,240
Wipe that off.

138
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:41,409
You talk about Zhao Li all the time.

139
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,750
Does he owe you a lot of money or what?

140
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:44,270
Do I really

141
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:45,600
resemble him that much?

142
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,480
No, there's a difference.

143
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,880
What kind of difference?

144
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,250
If Zhao Li were here,

145
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:52,120
I'd feel very secure.

146
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,000
Cut it out, you.

147
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,790
I'm highly capable too, alright?

148
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,190
I'm can also protect you.

149
00:09:01,630 --> 00:09:03,560
What beautiful sunset glow today.

150
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:07,440
Stop with all this sighing and blabbing.

151
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,240
Let's just go.

152
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:08,780
Hold on.

153
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:11,750
What now?

154
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:14,800
Take this.

155
00:09:15,390 --> 00:09:17,150
You bought me a bracelet? I won't wear it.

156
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,080
I didn't buy it.

157
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,790
It's Zhao Li's bracelet.

158
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:20,670
I think it suits you well.

159
00:09:20,670 --> 00:09:21,910
Then I definitely won't wear it,
since it's Zhao Li's.

160
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:24,440
Just give it a try.
You'll look cool with it on.

161
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,080
Don't throw it away,
now that you've put it on.

162
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,480
What Zhao Li used to wear

163
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,020
will keep you safe.

164
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,140
It's like he's everywhere, isn't it?

165
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,850
Let's go.

166
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:13,880
Something feels wrong.

167
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,130
But I don't find anything unusual.

168
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,250
There aren't any human sounds around.

169
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,320
Few people

170
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:23,320
reside in this town, right?

171
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,770
There's flowing water.

172
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,330
Flowers and trees, too.

173
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:30,370
There should be
sounds of birds and insects.

174
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,320
It really is very quiet here.

175
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:35,760
So quiet that it doesn't seem like
a human habitat.

176
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:51,550
You know how to read this?

177
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:52,120
No.

178
00:10:53,030 --> 00:10:53,750
Is everything fine?

179
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:54,440
No.

180
00:10:59,630 --> 00:11:00,760
What a lovely scent.

181
00:11:08,390 --> 00:11:09,320
Be careful.

182
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,580
It doesn't seem

183
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,640
like a normal butterfly.

184
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:17,750
It's okay.

185
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,850
This is an illusion.

186
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:22,920
Let's follow it to see what's going on.

187
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,150
This tune...

188
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:15,440
actually sounds familiar.

189
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:18,790
Let's go up there.

190
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:43,400
♪ Green willows cover my boudoir ♪

191
00:12:43,890 --> 00:12:48,280
♪ I adorn myself before the mirror ♪

192
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:52,800
♪ I put on a red dress every day ♪

193
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,480
There are demons producing illusions.

194
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:58,630
♪ When will the grass turn green again? ♪

195
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:56,030
I have a good idea

196
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,530
to conceal our presence from them.

197
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,240
What's your plan?

198
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:07,750
Off you go.

199
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:20,780
Let's move.

200
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:23,950
After we get in there,

201
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:24,980
follow me closely.

202
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:26,560
Don't touch anything.

203
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,200
If they find you

204
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,000
and catch you,

205
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:30,670
you'll have to spend the rest of your life

206
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,960
keeping them company in this town.

207
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,160
Even if they catch me,

208
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:34,750
you will come to my rescue.

209
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:35,630
It depends.

210
00:13:35,870 --> 00:13:37,000
I'll make an effort,

211
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,120
but if there's grave danger,

212
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,910
my priority will be keeping myself safe.

213
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:40,550
I don't buy it.

214
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:41,680
Suit yourself then.

215
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:44,910
Let me show you

216
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:46,110
what a night watchman

217
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,150
is capable of.

218
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:49,550
Shall I prepare background music

219
00:13:49,550 --> 00:13:50,360
for you?

220
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:51,790
Stay quiet and move ahead.

221
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,190
Make no noise as we tread.

222
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:54,000
Understood.

223
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:32,330
♪ Green willows cover my boudoir ♪

224
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:37,210
♪ I adorn myself before the mirror ♪

225
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:46,300
♪ I put on a red dress every day ♪

226
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:52,850
♪ Year after year,
my love never comes home ♪

227
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:59,910
♪ In the yellow earth mound,
I shall lie alone ♪

228
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:07,310
♪ When will the grass turn green again? ♪

229
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:16,650
This is all an illusion.

230
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,390
The demon that created it

231
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,590
is quite a character.

232
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:21,720
My love,

233
00:15:22,510 --> 00:15:23,440
you promised

234
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,840
to come back for me.

235
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,680
Why have you never returned?

236
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,660
What are you doing?

237
00:15:38,870 --> 00:15:40,750
Breaking a spell is like curing a disease.

238
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,600
The key is using the right charm
on the demon,

239
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,530
like applying the right medicine.

240
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:45,680
Something's wrong.

241
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,130
Zhao Li. Zhao Li!

242
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:50,600
Don't call me that.

243
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,750
Zhao Hengzhi, look.

244
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:53,670
It's that butterfly again.

